        "title": "[codex] clarify before_install hook scope",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nFixes #91593.\n\n- Clarify that `security.installPolicy` is the operator-owned install allow/block surface for CLI and Gateway-backed plugin install/update paths.\n- Reframe `before_install` as a plugin-runtime lifecycle hook that only runs in processes where plugin hooks are loaded.\n- Update CLI help/test wording and nearby test fixture language so future readers do not treat `before_install` as the primary enterprise install policy boundary.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `pnpm docs:list`\n- `pnpm docs:check-mdx`\n- `pnpm format:docs:check`\n- `pnpm docs:check-links`\n- `git diff --check`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/cli/plugins-cli.update.test.ts src/plugins/install.test.ts src/skills/lifecycle/install.test.ts`\n\n## Notes\n\n- `pnpm docs:list` initially hit restricted-network registry DNS failures in the fresh worktree; it passed after rerunning with network access so pnpm could populate the temp worktree dependencies.",
